NIT Trichy

National Institute of Technology Trichy (NITT) is situated in Tiruchirappalli division of Tamilnadu, established in 1964.The institute started with three engineering branches namely Civil, Mechanical and Electrical. NITT Trichy offers a total of 36 courses under 7 postgraduate and undergraduate degrees in the field of technology. More than 3,500 students of NITT are supervised and well thought of by 250 faculty members. For more Info visit here

  • campus tour

NIT Rourkela

Situated in the heart of Odisha, NIT Rourkela stands as a symbol of an educational mecca in the steel city of Rourkela. The college offers undergraduate, postgraduate and doctoral level courses in its campus. NIT Rourkela has a total of 44 courses taught in its Rourkela campus. The premium technological institution does not only have B.Tech and M.Tech level courses but also offers B.Sc+M.Sc, B.Tech+M.Tech and B.Arch courses. For more Info visit here

  • campus tour

NIT Suratkal

Established as the Karnataka Regional Engineering College or KREC in 1960.The institute is approved by AICTE for conducting technical education.The college offers a total of 32 UG and PG courses. NIT Surathkal not only offers B.Tech, M.Tech, MCA, M.Sc courses but also an MBA.NIT Surathkal has one of the most active placement cells within the engineering colleges of Karnataka. For more Info visit here

  • campus tour

NIT Warangal

National Institute of Technology, Warangal (NIT Warangal or NITW) is a public engineering college situated in Telangana. It was formerly known as Regional Engineering College and was renamed as the National Institute of Technology, Warangal in 2002.The institute is recognized as an Institute of National Importance by the Indian Government.For more Info visit here

  • campus tour

MNIT Jaipur

Established in 1963 as Malaviya Regional Engineering College (Jaipur), MNIT (Malaviya National Institute of Technology) . Jaipur runs with a mission to impart quality technical education at par with international standards. Apart from academics, MNIT Jaipur gives equal emphasis to research, and always focuses on coming up with the cutting edge technologies to meet the present and future challenges of technological development. For more Info visit here

  • campus tour

VNIT

Visvesvaraya National Institute of Technology (VNIT) was set up in 1960.. VNIT is known for the quality of education it imparts. VNIT Nagpur has three departments-Basic Science, Engineering and Architecture and Planning. The institute has bachelors, masters and doctoral degrees in architecture, engineering, and technology.VNIT Nagpur has more than 30 specialized laboratories and research centres. Roughly 798 students are admitted to the masters program every year For more Info visit here

  • campus tour

NIT Calicut

National Institute of Technology Calicut was established in 2007.The vision of NIT Calicut is to impart high-quality technical education and to provide its students with innovative research capabilities, basic engineering principles and managerial skills. The aim of National Institute of Technology Calicut is to impart education at par with global standards, NITC pays a lot of importance to research work For more Info visit here
